President Muhammadu Buhari has call on Nigerian youths to eschew all forms of religious cum ethnic discrimination for a better, prosperous nation. Buhari who made the appeal when he received APC Youth leaders who paid him a courtesy visit, also assured that his government is keen on including youths in the stream of governance. PMB according to a statement by
Mukhtar Jebba, Organising Secretary, APC Youths, was also reminded of some of his promises to the Nigerian youths by Sadiq Abubakar. On his part, Comrade Bello Bala Shagari, the President, National Youth Council of Nigeria (NYCN) assured President Muhammad Buhari that they are working towards harmonizing and unifying NYCN to end the ongoing crises. Shagari, who spoke when he was invited alongside leaders of the APC youth wing to a courtesy call on PMB, affirmed that his leadership believes in the unity of Nigerian youths.